                <h1>What is the SEC? Understanding Its Role & Importance</h1>
                <p>The SEC, or U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission, is a federal agency responsible for regulating the securities industry and protecting investors. It oversees stock and options exchanges, enforces securities laws, and ensures transparency in financial markets. By fostering fair practices, the SEC aims to maintain investor confidence.</p>
